00:25.780 --> 00:28.442
On his 35th birthday,

00:28.516 --> 00:31.713
l decided to tell Julius Benedict...

00:31.786 --> 00:34.721
the truth about himself.

00:38.526 --> 00:41.256
Julius already knew
that he was the product...

00:41.329 --> 00:43.763
of a scientific experiment...

00:43.831 --> 00:46.129
conducted by the American government.

00:48.469 --> 00:52.337
A top-secret experiment designed
to produce a physically,

00:52.406 --> 00:56.240
mentally and spiritually
advanced human being.

01:00.181 --> 01:02.911
He knew that,
unlike other little boys,

01:02.984 --> 01:06.818
he had not one, but six fathers--

01:06.887 --> 01:09.219
All very distinguished men...

01:09.290 --> 01:12.225
especially chosen for
their genetic excellence.

01:14.428 --> 01:16.362
And of course,

01:16.430 --> 01:19.627
he knew about Mary Ann Benedict,

01:22.069 --> 01:24.367
the remarkable young woman...

01:24.438 --> 01:27.271
who was selected to be his mother.

01:44.425 --> 01:48.122
Sadly, he had long lived
with the tragic knowledge...

01:48.195 --> 01:52.996
that his mother died
while giving birth to him.

01:56.904 --> 01:59.702
Now, what Julius did not know,

01:59.774 --> 02:02.709
not until this very moment,

02:02.777 --> 02:07.043
was that about a minute
after he was born...

02:07.114 --> 02:11.881
his mother gave birth
to another baby boy.

02:59.834 --> 03:02.359
l have a brother?

03:02.436 --> 03:04.666
Ya.

03:04.739 --> 03:07.333
He was sent to an orphanage
in Los Angeles...

03:07.408 --> 03:10.707
at the same time
l brought you here to the island.

03:12.646 --> 03:16.446
Julius had spent his entire life
here on the island,

03:16.517 --> 03:20.044
helping me with my research.

03:20.121 --> 03:23.488
l always thought he was happy,
and had no desire to leave.

03:23.557 --> 03:25.650
How wrong l was.

03:25.726 --> 03:28.820
l must find him.

03:31.432 --> 03:34.333
Julius, Julius!
Wait, wait.

03:36.303 --> 03:39.033
l couldn't believe he was going.

03:40.307 --> 03:44.175
He wasn't equipped to deal
with the outside world.

03:45.446 --> 03:48.745
All of his knowledge was from books.

03:49.917 --> 03:52.818
Julius could speak 12 languages.

03:52.887 --> 03:55.355
He excelled in history, science,

03:55.422 --> 03:58.016
mathematics, literature.

03:58.092 --> 04:00.925
He was pure in body and in spirit.

04:00.995 --> 04:02.087
Ahhh!

04:02.163 --> 04:05.155
But for the first time,

04:05.232 --> 04:07.427
Julius would not listen to me.

04:07.501 --> 04:11.028
He's probably just like me.

04:19.814 --> 04:24.717
The nearest island with
an airport was 27 miles away.

04:27.488 --> 04:30.787
But Julius did not care.

04:30.858 --> 04:33.486
He had become obsessed
with the idea...

04:33.561 --> 04:37.053
that his brother, Vincent,
was in some kind of trouble...

04:37.131 --> 04:40.430
and desperately needed his help.

04:44.305 --> 04:46.500
Honey, l'm home!

04:46.574 --> 04:48.769
- Oh, no!
- Oh, no.

04:48.843 --> 04:51.311
- Get going!
- l'm going.

05:15.669 --> 05:17.694
Oh, hello, hello!

05:17.771 --> 05:20.205
Oh, my goodness!

05:26.947 --> 05:29.472
Good-bye.

05:39.093 --> 05:42.085
- We're gonna be late for work.
- l need my horoscope.

05:42.162 --> 05:45.529
- Yeah, horoscope.
- ''Your judgment is at its peak today.

05:45.599 --> 05:48.762
Use it wisely,
and romance will follow.''

05:48.836 --> 05:52.431
- Ooh, good one.
- l hope so.

05:52.506 --> 05:54.701
Ladies!

05:54.775 --> 05:57.903
- Vince!
- l thought you broke up with him.

05:57.978 --> 05:59.946
l did, l did!

06:03.250 --> 06:07.619
- You don't mind if l talk
to your sister, do you?
- She doesn't mind.

06:07.688 --> 06:09.883
Don't give him any money.

06:09.957 --> 06:14.758
Uh, no, no, l promised Marnie
l wouldn't give you any money.

06:19.266 --> 06:21.996
Don't look at me like--

06:22.069 --> 06:24.867
Don't do that thing
with your eyes.

06:24.939 --> 06:28.534
l'm not even supposed
to be here with you.

06:28.609 --> 06:32.067
You are here,
and so am l.

06:32.146 --> 06:34.740
Maybe millions
of people go by,

06:34.815 --> 06:37.079
but they all
disappear from view.

06:37.151 --> 06:40.882
l only have eyes
for you, Linda.

06:40.955 --> 06:43.890
l only have
eyes for you.

06:45.592 --> 06:48.857
Mmm.

06:48.929 --> 06:52.956
- lt's the baby Klane!
- What?

06:55.536 --> 06:57.527
- Hi.
- Hi.

06:57.604 --> 07:00.129
- Can l help you?
- Uh, yeah.

07:00.207 --> 07:02.835
Where's the little shit?

07:02.910 --> 07:05.435
You'll have to be
more specific...

07:05.512 --> 07:07.946
concerning the clientele.

07:08.015 --> 07:10.006
Benedict.

07:10.084 --> 07:13.247
Oh, he wouldn't come in here.

07:13.320 --> 07:15.413
- lsn't that right, Marnie?
- Who, Vincent?

07:16.857 --> 07:20.759
That weasel? That creep?

07:20.828 --> 07:24.491
l wouldn't serve him if he crawled in
on his hands and knees.

07:27.301 --> 07:30.668
Take out the papers
and the trash

07:30.738 --> 07:34.265
Or you don't get
no spending cash

07:34.408 --> 07:37.002
lf you don't scrub
that kitchen floor

07:37.077 --> 07:41.514
You ain't gonna
rock and roll no more

